caption: I absolutely love this place. I go regularly and never grow tired of their food. I have tried other pad Thai from other Thai restaurants, and others really don't compare to Thai Oscars. I like the spider maki, spring rolls, egg rolls, and fried leek dumplings as appetizers. I still need to try more. Thai iced coffee and tea is really good as well.

Absolutely bad Thai. Bad panang curry, bad soup, bad fried rice (way too much soy sauce and oil), bad Pad Se Yu - greasy, bad lettuce wraps (stale noodles, tasteless chicken and my wife's chicken had bone on it), bad tempura - the worst tempura I have ever had.  It was breaded fried veggies, like if my mom made fried veggies, I've had better tempura at the county fair... Bad.

This place is conveniently located across the street from my therapist. I go once a week - it's that good! The staff is always so polite and very accommodating. Great lunch special and happy portions. I usually leave with a snack portion of my pad thai to go.

Great food here. I get carryout from here a lot. I particularly like the Thai Oscar curry fried rice. Great combo! Also, the pad thai is really solid. I like to compare Thai places based on their pad thai since it's so ubiquitous. So take that as a good sign they care about the quality of their dishes. OH and the fried tofu sticks appetizer is really awesome.

Good Thai place in an area with a lot of Thai restaurants.  My favorite thing about this place is the turtle sushi which isn't actually turtle meat, but they carve a turtle shape out of various sushi and veggies!

This is my favorite thai n sushi place in the city by far and ive been to a ton of thai n sushi joints. This place has THE BEST crab rangoon and I absolutely love their Woonsen Pad Thai with chicken. Now their sushi isnt the best but it always is a nice complement to the thai food, I think the maki choices with shrimp tempura suck bc their tempura batter isnt up to par. But all the other maki choices are yummy.
